      • getSets

        @GET
@Path("getSets")
@Produces("application/json")
public javax.ws.rs.core.Response getSets​(@QueryParam("ooid")
                                         java.lang.Long ooid,
                                         @QueryParam("measurementnames")
                                         java.lang.String measurementnames,
                                         @QueryParam("searchcolumns")
                                         java.lang.String searchcolumns,
                                         @QueryParam("searchvalues")
                                         java.lang.String searchvalues,
                                         @QueryParam("starttime")
                                         java.lang.String starttime,
                                         @QueryParam("endtime")
                                         java.lang.String endtime,
                                         @QueryParam("startset")
                                         long startset,
                                         @QueryParam("limit")
                                         int limit,
                                         @QueryParam("orderby")
                                         java.lang.String orderby,
                                         @QueryParam("order")
                                         java.lang.String order,
                                         @QueryParam("recursive")
                                         boolean recursive,
                                         @QueryParam("deflatt")
                                         boolean deflatt,
                                         @QueryParam("countOnly")
                                         boolean countOnly)
        Gets datasets matching the given criteria from the data for observedobject identified by ooid.DEV NOTE: requests with parameters are untested
        Parameters:
        ooid - ID of the observed object to get data from
        measurementnames - List of measurementnames to fetch, separated by comma
        searchcolumns - List of columns to search in, separated by comma
        searchvalues - List of strings to search for, can use regex as in a regular LIKE comparison: column LIKE string AND column2 LIKE string2
        starttime - Starttime of data
        endtime - Endtime of data
        startset - Id of the start set to get date from
        limit - Limit of datasets to recive
        orderby - Order By Flag ASC or DESC
        order - Order of the result (ASC or DESC)
        recursive - true to get data of the observed object and all childs
        deflatt - if set to true data will be deflattend if possible
        countOnly - if true the datasets are count
        Returns:
        List of datasets in form [ Object{ col1 : colval1, col2 : conval1 }, Object{ col1 : colval2, col2 : colval2 } ]
